# PropTypes for Type Checking

React provides a built-in typechecking feature called **PropTypes**. It helps catch bugs by validating the types of props passed to a component.

First, install the package (it's not included in React core anymore):

```bash
npm install prop-types
```

Then import and define `propTypes` on your component.

```jsx
import PropTypes from 'prop-types';

function Greeting({ name, age }) {
  return <h1>{name} is {age}</h1>;
}

Greeting.propTypes = {
  name: PropTypes.string.isRequired,
  age: PropTypes.number
};
```

If a prop of the wrong type is passed, React logs a warning in the console (in development mode).

slides.codeSnippet:
import PropTypes from 'prop-types';

function Button({ text, color }) {
  return <button style={{ backgroundColor: color }}>{text}</button>;
}

Button.propTypes = {
  text: PropTypes.string.isRequired,
  color: PropTypes.string
};

Button.defaultProps = {
  color: 'blue'
};
